==English==
===Adjective===
'''out-and-out''' (''used only before a noun; no [[comparative]] or [[superlative]]'')

#{{idiom}} [[Complete]], [[utter]].
#:''He is an '''out-and-out''' idiot.''

===Quotations===
'''1998'''. "I'm sure most of the people in this room will share the same view, but even as an out-and-out atheist one can't help noticing that the role of a god has had an enormously profound impact on human history over many, many centuries." &mdash; Douglas Adams, speech at Cambridge, UK. [http://www.biota.org/people/douglasadams/index.html]


